{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "In addition to covert surveillance, overt interrogation can also cause behavioral chilling.",
    "Interrogation could involve excessive requests for user information by the platform-either on signup or during use-or users badgering others with personal questions.",
    "If users feel pressured to provide information, even if they refuse, it is still a discomfiting invasion of privacy (Solove, 2006), and children may be more prone to oversharing personal information (Reed & Joseff, 2022).",
    "Overall, chilling effects will impact everyone uncomfortable with surveillance, but especially those who need to keep some aspect of their identity private, including activists and people exploring their identity.",
    "Surveillance can also be performed by other IXR users, workplaces and schools, and hackers."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "If users feel pressured to provide information, even if they refuse, it is still a discomfiting invasion of privacy (Solove, 2006), and children may be more prone to oversharing personal information (Reed & Joseff, 2022)."
